This paper discusses the problem of digital preservation of web content, which falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper also discusses the need for converting web content into compatible formats, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and cryptography (cs.CR) techniques. The paper also mentions the difficulty of finding and installing plug-ins, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) research. Finally, the paper discusses the transformation of image formats, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) research.
